It’s time to move your Feral File NFTs and crypto to your web3 wallet

it is basically impossible to get the range without knowing anything. 
in the FFV1.0 design, we make the id starts from a hash of the artwork file itself.
in V2, we make the tokenID starts by a series id from server. That means you still need to check the start id and counter by our supply.
the token id need to be unique by contract. and it also need to be unique by our system. with this limitation, we can not just straight forwardedly make the id starts from 1, for example.

I don't really need to know the exact range. If I could construct an ID, then I could compare the first 10-15 chars.
